Package chess

Class Piece

java.lang.Object
chess.Piece
Direct Known Subclasses:
Bishop, King, Knight, Pawn, Queen, Rook
public abstract class Piece
extends java.lang.Object
Piece is an abstract class that is part of a Board (for chess). A Piece has a current location on the board of a specific size, and it has its location set as {-1,- 1} when it is killed (moved out of the board). A Piece is an abstract superclass for all the actual chess Pieces, such as Pawn, Knight, etc.
Author:
Seok Yim, Mae Khaled

  • Field Details

    • currentLocation

      public int[] currentLocation
      This is the current location for the Piece. CurrentLocation[0] is the row index, and CurrentLocation[1] is the column index.

    • color

      public char color
      This is the color of the Piece. It has a value of either 'w' or 'b', which stand for white and black, respectively.

  • Method Details

    • isValidMove

      public abstract boolean isValidMove​(int er, int ec, Piece[][] chessboard, int turn_number)
      Checks whether a specific move for a Piece is valid. Assumes the move is not repeating the current Piece location. Assumes that er and ec are between 0 and 7, inclusive on both sides.
      Parameters:
      er - ending/final row index for this move
      ec - ending/final column index for this move
      chessboard - Piece[][] chessboard
      turn_number - the number of turns passed since the start of game
      Returns:
      true if is a valid move, false otherwise

    • move

      public void move​(int er, int ec)
      Moves Piece to a specific location. Assumes that the move to be made is valid ( does no condition checking).
      Parameters:
      er - ending/final row index after move
      ec - ending/final column index after move

    • kill

      public void kill()
      Kills the Piece. Here, kill means removing the Piece from the board by settings its current location to {-1,-1}.

    • canReach

      public abstract boolean canReach​(int er, int ec, Piece[][] chessboard)
      Determines whether a Piece can reach a specific location to kill an enemy if the enemy were to be there.
      Parameters:
      er - ending row index
      ec - ending column index
      chessboard - Piece[][] chessboard
      Returns:
      true if the piece can reach the specified location to possibly kill an enemy, false otherwise

    • leavesKingChecked

      public static boolean leavesKingChecked​(Piece[][] chessboard, char color)
      Checks whether a specific move leaves its own team's king checked. This method should only be called when the move is deemed to be valid in any other way(satisfying a piece specific requirement, not killing its own teammate, a Pawn not jumping over other piece, etc.). All subclasses of Piece should call this method inside their isValidMove() method.
      Parameters:
      color - either 'w' or 'b', denoting whose king is being observed for their safety
      chessboard - Piece[][] chessboard
      Returns:
      true if a king of the specified color is checked, false otherwise

    • findKing

      public static King findKing​(Piece[][] chessboard, char color)
      Finds the King for the specified color.
      Parameters:
      chessboard - Piece[][] chessboard
      color - color of King
      Returns:
      King of the specified color

    • getAllPossibleMoves

      public abstract java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer[]> getAllPossibleMoves​(Piece[][] chessboard, int turn_number)
      Returns all possible moves that a specific piece is capable of making. The returned possible moves might be blocked by other pieces (so they could be considered invalid), but they are ensured to be moves within the board.
      Parameters:
      chessboard - Piece[][] chessboard
      turn_number - the number of turns passed since the start of the game
      Returns:
      the ArrayList of Integer[] of length 2 containing the row and column indices of the final location for the possible move
